<div class="jumbotron a-story-main" style="text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="green-txt" style="text-align: left;">
            our story</h1>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 25px; height: 100%;">
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-sm-4" style="position: relative;">
                <img src="~/images/home_new/aboutus/story_1.png" alt="iq media founders, john derham, lakshmi venkataswamy" />
                <div class="a-story">
                    <h3>
                        A Napkin and Two Barstools</h3>
                    John and Lakshmi teamed up nearly 25 years ago, forging an inseparable relationship that
                    made them pioneers of big data before it was a trendy word to use. Recognizing that
                    there were unique technology challenges in the media monitoring industry that nobody
                    was trying to overcome, John and Lakshmi felt that these issues were solvable with
                    the same approaches to data models and infrastructures that had been developed for
                    the banking industry. The two of them developed the entire plan of iQ media on the
                    bar napkin. <a href="http://blog.iqmediacorp.com/intro-to-the-iq-media-blog-the-beginning-of-media-intelligence/" target="_blank" class="green-txt">Learn more about their story.</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-sm-4"><img src="~/images/home_new/aboutus/story_2.png" alt="media intelligence story" /><div class="a-story"><h3>The Birth of Media Intelligence</h3>
                    Revolutions often come from an outlier, driven by someone who takes a very different
                    approach. John and Lakshmi felt they could provide this different approach to media
                    monitoring. Most importantly, they wanted to advance the old monitoring platforms into
                    the "Media Intelligence Age." The revolution of iQ media and <a href="http://blog.iqmediacorp.com/what-media-intelligence-really-means/" target="_blank" class="green-txt">the media intelligence
                    age</a> was born in an office over John's garage in rural Pennsylvania in 2010.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-sm-4">
                <img src="~/images/home_new/aboutus/story_3.png" alt="iq media investors, gmh ventures" />
                <div class="a-story">
                    <h3>
                        iQ Investment</h3>
                    In 2011, iQ media received its first investment from GMH Ventures. iQ showed promise
                    and innovation which captured GMH's interest and ultimately resulted in their involvement
                    in our evolution. They were able to foresee the growth and expansion that was in store
                    for iQ and knew they had to take this opportunity to invest in the future of media intelligence.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="clear: both;">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="height: 100%;">
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-sm-4">
                <img src="~/images/home_new/aboutus/story_4.png" alt="founding team at iq media" />
                <div class="a-story">
                    <h3>
                        Garage Sale</h3>
                    2012 ushered in big changes and improvements and spurred the decision to move the
                    company from above John's garage to an office in Doylestown, PA. During this time,
                    the company continued to grow and develop. Advancing in technology helped begin to
                    make a name for iQ media among the top names in media monitoring.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-sm-4">
                <img src="~/images/home_new/aboutus/story_5.png" alt="iq media offices" />
